2.21pm And what a performance this was. It's now the second-highest team total of the 2019 World Cup. But Australia won't give up just yet, they showed us in Mohali in March that they can take down India's big scores, and the pitch, too, hasn't behaved as badly as it looked in the morning. Big props to Shikhar Dhawan and Virat Kohli for setting the base, and after that India's last three batsmen - Pandya, Dhoni and Rahul - added 86 runs off 44 deliveries. That's what made the difference between a 330-score and a 350-one. We'll be back super soon with the chase. Don't forget to enjoy our Match Day show on the homepage.

Dhawan: Played it smartly and calmly (laughs). I like playing here at The Oval, and I love ICC tournaments. We're in a great position now. Bouncy wickets suit my game. I feel it's enough runs on the board. Our experience and pace will do well."
